ics, and discuss his navigations between British and Italian identities.  aMode of access: Internet via World Wide Web.  aIn English.0 aDescription based on online resource; title from PDF title page (publisher's Web site, viewed 06. Mrz 2024) 0aPoets, EnglishxHomes and hauntszItaly. 4aLiterature Studies 2020. 7aLITERARY CRITICISM / European / Italian.2bisacsh  aAnglo-Italian identity.  aByronic lyricism.  aByronic satire.  aByron’s dramas.  aByron’s letters.  aByron’s narrative art.  ahistory.  aplace.  apolitics.  areligion/Catholicism.1 aAngeletti, Gioia, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aBeatty, Bernard, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGraham, Peter W., econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aGross, Jonathan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHalmi, Nicholas, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aHorová, Mirka, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aPala, Mauro, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRawes, Alan, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aRawes, Alan, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSaglia, Diego, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aSaglia, Diego, eeditor.4edt4http://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/edt1 aSchmidt, Arnold Anthony, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb1 aStabler, Jane, econtributor.4ctb4https://id.loc.gov/vocabulary/relators/ctb08iTitle is part of eBook package:dDe GruytertManchester University Press 2018 eBook-Packagez978311128277040uhttps://doi.org/10.7765/978152612607840uhttps://www.degruyter.com/isbn/9781526126078423Coveruhttps://www.degruyter.com/document/cover/isbn/9781526126078/original  a978-3-11-128277-0  Manchester University Press 2018